The mining lease for LSE-listed Gem Diamonds’ Letšeng mine has been renewed by the Government of the Kingdom of Lesotho for 10 years. Gem Diamonds exists Botswana Following
a successful statutory negotiation process, the terms of the renewed mining
lease were agreed with the Lesotho Mining Board and include the following
material terms “The mining lease renewal will
allow the Letšeng mine to continue to make a very significant economic and
social contribution to the people of Lesotho,” says Gem Diamonds CEO Clifford
Elphick, who thanked the Government of Lesotho for its ongoing support. “We look forward to continuing the shared value creation long into the future.” 